{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6151e8631540bc3dc5113c77", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fec2b295b085ab6eb8f"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "53", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "A heavy, flexible uniform chain of length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03c0</mi><mi>r</mi></math> and mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>\u03bb</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03c0</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math>lies in a smooth semicircular tube <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math>of the radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>. Assuming a slight disturbance to start the chain in motion, find the velocity&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> with which it will emerge from the end&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> of the tube.<br />\r<br />\r<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/jee_main/images/EM0014750_Question_1_1.jpg\" style=\"width: 249px; height: 164px;\" />", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "Hi3dP", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>4</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>&#8289;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mtext>&#960;</mtext></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mtext>&#960;</mtext><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "DQdZT", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>3</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>r</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mtext>&#960;</mtext></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mtext>&#960;</mtext><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "OiMfg", "text": "<math> <mrow> <msqrt> <mn>2</mn> <mtext>g</mtext> <mi></mi><mi></mi><mi></mi><mi></mi><mi>r</mi><mo>\u2061</mo> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>\u03c0</mtext> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>\u03c0</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </mfenced> </msqrt> </mrow> </math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "MKmii", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>5</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>r</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mtext>\u03c0</mtext></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mtext>\u03c0</mtext><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "Since friction absent, we can apply the law of conservation of energy. Centre of gravity of a semicircular arc is at a distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03c0</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math> from the centre.<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Initial potential energy</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">\u03bb</mtext><mtext>\u03c0</mtext><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">r</mtext></mrow></mfenced><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">r</mtext></mrow><mtext>\u03c0</mtext></mfrac></mfenced></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Final potential energy</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">\u03bb</mtext><mtext>\u03c0</mtext><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">r</mtext></mrow></mfenced><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mtext>\u03c0</mtext><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">r</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math><br /><br />When the chain is completely slipped off the tube, all the links of the chain have the same velocity <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>.<br /><br /><u><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/jee_main/images/EM0014750_AnsExp1_1.jpg\" /></strong></u><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Kinetic energy of chain</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">\u03bb</mtext><mtext>\u03c0</mtext><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">r</mtext></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>From COE,</mtext><mspace width=\"0.5em\"></mspace><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">\u03bb</mtext><mtext>\u03c0</mtext><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">rg</mtext><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mtext>\u03c0</mtext></mrow><mtext>r</mtext></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">\u03bb</mtext><mtext>\u03c0</mtext><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">r</mtext></mrow></mfenced><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">g</mtext><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mtext>\u03c0</mtext><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">r</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">\u03bb</mtext><mtext>\u03c0</mtext><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">r</mtext></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>From which we find,</mtext><mspace width=\"0.5em\"></mspace><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>r</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mtext>\u03c0</mtext></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mtext>\u03c0</mtext><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></msq